{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17606693","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17606693"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:15:13+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:15:13+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15930"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15930","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15930"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8621"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72838"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8621","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8621"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15930"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58308"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4933"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"8673"},{"type":"tags","id":"8676"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20648"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20651"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72838","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/72838"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe permanent kidney (metanephros) forms during early human development through complex interactions between embryonic tissues.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the origin and timing of metanephros development?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Develops from intermediate mesoderm in week five","Develops from mesonephric duct in week three","Develops from surface ectoderm in week eight","Develops from lateral plate mesoderm in week six","Develops from endoderm in week four"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eintermediate mesoderm\u003C/strong\u003E gives rise to the metanephros beginning in week five of development. This process involves complex signalling between the ureteric bud and surrounding metanephric mesenchyme.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Emesonephric duct\u003C/strong\u003E gives rise to the ureteric bud but is not the direct origin of the metanephros\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esurface ectoderm\u003C/strong\u003E does not contribute to kidney development\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Elateral plate mesoderm\u003C/strong\u003E forms other structures like body wall and limb components\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eendoderm\u003C/strong\u003E forms the gut tube and associated organs, not the kidneys\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe ureteric bud undergoes repeated branching to form the collecting system, while the metanephric mesenchyme forms the nephrons through mesenchymal-to-epithelial transition. This coordinated development is essential for normal kidney formation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The metanephros develops from intermediate mesoderm during week five of embryological development","The ureteric bud induces formation of the metanephric blastema which forms nephrons","The collecting system develops from the ureteric bud through branching morphogenesis"],"references":["Sadler TW. Langman\u0027s Medical Embryology: Wolters Kluwer; 2015.","Rehman S, Ahmed D. Embryology, Kidney, Bladder, and Ureter. In: StatPearls [Online].  [Updated 2023 Aug 8]. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK547747/"]},"rela